               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-379-person3112">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HENRY PEARCE
               <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3112" type="surname" value="HENRY PEARCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3112" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3112" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Rosamond-place, Limehouse. On the 21st of August, early in the morning, the shawl was on the neck of my child, which a friend was carrying - he is not here; I had occasion to stop behind, and as I came on I saw the prisoner take the shawl off the ground; I said, "My friend, this is my property;" he said, "I wish you may get it," and run across the road-I followed; he said, "You may run, and be d - d;" I cannot say that he saw it fall from the child, which had gone on about thirty yards.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Where is your friend? A. Not here; I have not seen him since - I told the prisoner it was mine, and he ran off with it; I do not believe he saw it dropped - I had asked him about a minute before what he stood there for; this was before he took the shawl.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-379-person3113">
                  JAMES 
                  PYE
               <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3113" type="surname" value="PYE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3113" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3113" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I took the prisoner in Penny's-fields, Poplar, running; the prosecutor was following, calling Stop thief! I took the shawl from under his jacket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-379-person3114">
                  JOHN 
                  BENT
               <interp inst="t18320906-379-person3114" type="surname" value="BENT"></interp>
